Note:
XML Translation Round-Trip Probe

End-to-end proof that the XML translation pipeline is REAL, not a skeleton:

    XML source
      -> xml_lexer    (tokenize: tags, attributes, text, entities, CDATA, comments)
      -> xml_parser   (build XML element-tree AST, match tags, single root)
      -> xml_semantic (well-formedness + namespace prefix resolution + depth)
      -> xml_to_hir   (lower XML AST to the canonical HIR literal model)
      -> hir_to_xml   (emit HIR back to well-formed XML text with escaping)

The probe feeds a representative document containing a namespaced root with a
declared prefix, an attribute whose value carries an entity reference, a
namespaced child element, text content carrying an entity reference, a CDATA
section, a comment, and an empty (self-closing) element. It then:

  1. Parses and runs the semantic analyzer, asserting the well-formed document
     is accepted and that an analogous document with an UNDECLARED namespace
     prefix is rejected (proving namespace resolution is real).
  2. Translates the source to HIR and asserts the HIR root is a dictionary
     literal whose "_tag" is the element name, whose attribute is reachable
     by name, and whose text child de-escapes the entity reference to the raw
     byte (proving entity decoding survives lowering).
  3. Emits the HIR back to XML text and asserts the text is non-empty and
     begins with '<'.
  4. Re-parses the emitted XML back into HIR and asserts the two HIR trees are
     STRUCTURALLY EQUAL via a recursive comparator. Structural equality
     (rather than byte equality) is the correct semantic-equivalence check
     because the emitter pretty-prints and the byte form differs from the
     compact input while the meaning is identical.

Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed). No exit_with_code.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/xml/xml_to_hir.runa" as XmlFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/xml/xml_parser.runa" as XmlParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/xml/xml_semantic.runa" as XmlSemantic
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/xml/hir_to_xml.runa" as XmlBackend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HIR dictionary lookup by string key (content comparison)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The XML element dictionary stores "_tag", flat attribute entries, "_attributes",
and "_children" in an order that depends on the element's attribute set. Looking
up values by content-compared key rather than positional index makes the probe's
assertions robust to that ordering, exactly as the backend's get_dict_hir_value
does.
@End Reasoning

Process called "dict_lookup" takes hir_dict as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let entries be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with hir_dict

    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with entries
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than count:
        Let entry be proc get_at from List with entries, index
        Let entry_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 0
        Let entry_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 8

        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with entry_key, key

        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return entry_value
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Structural HIR equality (semantic equivalence of two XML-derived trees)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Two XML documents are semantically equal when their HIR projections are
structurally equal: same node kind at every position, same scalar payloads, same
key/value pairing for the element dictionaries (order-preserving, which the
lowering guarantees), and same element ordering for the children arrays.
Comparing the HIR trees rather than the raw text is whitespace- and
formatting-insensitive, so it proves round-trip fidelity without being fooled by
the emitter's pretty-printing.
@End Reasoning

Process called "hir_equal" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        If b is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let kind_a be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with a
    Let kind_b be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with b

    If kind_a is not equal to kind_b:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Dictionary literals: compare entry count, then key+value pairwise
    If kind_a is equal to HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL from HIR:
        Let entries_a be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with a
        Let entries_b be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with b

        If entries_a is equal to 0:
            If entries_b is equal to 0:
                Return 1
            End If
            Return 0
        End If

        If entries_b is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If

        Let count_a be proc size from List with entries_a
        Let count_b be proc size from List with entries_b

        If count_a is not equal to count_b:
            Return 0
        End If

        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count_a:
            Let entry_a be proc get_at from List with entries_a, i
            Let entry_b be proc get_at from List with entries_b, i

            Let key_a be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry_a, 0
            Let key_b be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry_b, 0
            Let keys_match be proc string_equals from StringCore with key_a, key_b

            If keys_match is not equal to 1:
                Return 0
            End If

            Let val_a be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry_a, 8
            Let val_b be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry_b, 8
            Let vals_match be proc hir_equal with val_a, val_b

            If vals_match is not equal to 1:
                Return 0
            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Array literals: compare element count, then elements pairwise
    If kind_a is equal to HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL from HIR:
        Let elems_a be proc get_list_elements from HIR with a
        Let elems_b be proc get_list_elements from HIR with b

        If elems_a is equal to 0:
            If elems_b is equal to 0:
                Return 1
            End If
            Return 0
        End If

        If elems_b is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If

        Let ecount_a be proc size from List with elems_a
        Let ecount_b be proc size from List with elems_b

        If ecount_a is not equal to ecount_b:
            Return 0
        End If

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than ecount_a:
            Let el_a be proc get_at from List with elems_a, j
            Let el_b be proc get_at from List with elems_b, j
            Let el_match be proc hir_equal with el_a, el_b

            If el_match is not equal to 1:
                Return 0
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Scalar literals (HIR_LITERAL): compare value_type tag, then payload
    If kind_a is equal to HIR_LITERAL from HIR:
        Let tag_a be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with a, 48
        Let tag_b be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with b, 48

        If tag_a is not equal to tag_b:
            Return 0
        End If

        Let payload_a be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with a, 40
        Let payload_b be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with b, 40

        Note: String and float payloads are string pointers; compare by content
        If tag_a is equal to HIR_LITERAL_KIND_STRING from HIR:
            Return proc string_equals from StringCore with payload_a, payload_b
        End If

        If tag_a is equal to HIR_LITERAL_KIND_FLOAT from HIR:
            Return proc string_equals from StringCore with payload_a, payload_b
        End If

        Note: Integer/boolean/null payloads are compared by raw value
        If payload_a is equal to payload_b:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "XML translation round-trip"

    Note:
    Representative document: a namespaced root declaring its own prefix, an
    attribute whose value carries an entity reference, a namespaced child with
    text content carrying an entity reference, a CDATA section, a comment, and a
    self-closing element. The lexer resolves &amp; -> '&' and &lt; -> '<' inside
    text and attribute values before the parser ever sees them.
    :End Note
    Let source be "<doc:root xmlns:doc=\"urn:example\" label=\"a&amp;b\"><doc:item id=\"1\">Remember &amp; relax</doc:item><![CDATA[<raw> & data]]><!-- a note --><br/></doc:root>"

    Note: --- Stage 0: parse + semantic validation ---
    Let ast be proc parse_xml from XmlParser with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser produced XML AST", ast

    Let valid be proc validate_xml_ast_default from XmlSemantic with ast
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "semantic pass accepts well-formed namespaced document", valid, 1

    Note: Semantic pass must REJECT an element using an undeclared namespace prefix
    Let bad_source be "<root><undef:child>x</undef:child></root>"
    Let bad_ast be proc parse_xml from XmlParser with bad_source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser produced undeclared-prefix AST", bad_ast
    Let bad_valid be proc validate_xml_ast_default from XmlSemantic with bad_ast
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "semantic pass rejects undeclared namespace prefix", bad_valid, 0

    Note: --- Stage 1: source -> HIR ---
    Let hir1 be proc translate_xml_to_hir from XmlFrontend with source, 0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend produced HIR root", hir1

    Let root_kind be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with hir1
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "HIR root is dictionary literal", root_kind, HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL from HIR

    Note: The element's "_tag" must be the qualified root name
    Let tag_val be proc dict_lookup with hir1, "_tag"
    Let tag_str be proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with tag_val
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "root _tag is 'doc:root'", tag_str, "doc:root"

    Note: The attribute value must be reachable by name and de-escaped (&amp; -> &)
    Let label_val be proc dict_lookup with hir1, "label"
    Let label_str be proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with label_val
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "attribute 'label' de-escapes to 'a&b'", label_str, "a&b"

    Note: The xmlns:doc declaration is itself an attribute and reachable by name
    Let ns_val be proc dict_lookup with hir1, "xmlns:doc"
    Let ns_str be proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with ns_val
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "namespace decl 'xmlns:doc' is 'urn:example'", ns_str, "urn:example"

    Note: Children list must exist and be an array literal
    Let children_val be proc dict_lookup with hir1, "_children"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "element has _children", children_val
    Let children_kind be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with children_val
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "_children is array literal", children_kind, HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL from HIR

    Note:
    Children (with default comment/PI stripping) are: the doc:item element, the
    CDATA string, and the self-closing br element. The comment is dropped because
    preserve_comments defaults to 0. That is three children.
    :End Note
    Let children_elems be proc get_list_elements from HIR with children_val
    Let children_count be proc size from List with children_elems
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "element has 3 surviving children", children_count, 3

    Note: First child is the doc:item element; its text de-escapes the entity
    Let item_node be proc get_at from List with children_elems, 0
    Let item_kind be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with item_node
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "first child is element dictionary", item_kind, HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL from HIR

    Let item_tag_val be proc dict_lookup with item_node, "_tag"
    Let item_tag_str be proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with item_tag_val
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "child _tag is 'doc:item'", item_tag_str, "doc:item"

    Let item_children_val be proc dict_lookup with item_node, "_children"
    Let item_children_elems be proc get_list_elements from HIR with item_children_val
    Let text_node be proc get_at from List with item_children_elems, 0
    Let text_kind be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with text_node
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "child text node is a literal", text_kind, HIR_LITERAL from HIR

    Let text_str be proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with text_node
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "text content de-escapes '&amp;' to '&'", text_str, "Remember & relax"

    Note: The de-escaped text must contain a literal '&' byte (38) at the right spot
    Let amp_byte be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text_str, 9
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "text byte[9] is '&' (38)", amp_byte, 38

    Note: --- Stage 2: HIR -> XML text ---
    Let emitted be proc hir_to_xml from XmlBackend with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "backend produced XML text", emitted

    Let emitted_len be proc string_length from StringCore with emitted
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "emitted XML is non-empty", emitted_len, 0

    Note: --- Stage 3: re-parse emitted XML -> HIR, assert structurally equal ---
    Let hir2 be proc translate_xml_to_hir from XmlFrontend with emitted, 0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parse of emitted XML produced HIR", hir2

    Let structurally_equal be proc hir_equal with hir1, hir2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip HIR is structurally equal", structurally_equal, 1

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process
